# NOTE: internal/ebpf/bpf/vmlinux.h is COMMITTED (not ignored). CO-RE relocates
# field offsets at load time, so one checked-in header serves every kernel/arch
# and makes the Docker build hermetic — devs on macOS/Windows (no kernel BTF) can
# build. Regenerate only when probes start reading new kernel structs:
# `make vmlinux` on a Linux host, or `./docker-build.sh vmlinux`.
